 Legislature finds that it is in the best interest of South Dakota school children that local school districts employ school counselors, who are certified in accordance with the certification requirements of the South Dakota Board of Education, to provide counseling services to students. Section 2. Every school district shall provide counseling services to all public school students in the district. Each district shall employ no less than one certified counselor for every four hundred fifty students. School districts may cooperate to provide counseling services to meet the minimum requirements. Section 3. School districts receiving state aid to education pursuant to chapter 13-13 shall be reimbursed by the general state aid formula at a rate of thirty dollars per student, up to one thousand five hundred students, for certified counselors and counseling services. Section 4. The secretary of the Department of Education and Cultural Affairs shall promulgate rules, pursuant to chapter 1-26, to specify levels or ratios of certified counselor services, reimbursement procedures, and other provisions of this Act."}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 18070, "action_date": "2003-01-29T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 96046, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/96046.pdf", "status_text": "First read in Senate and referred to", "journal_page": 230, "committee_id_action": 799, "committee_id_assigned": 774, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 18070, "action_date": "2003-02-06T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 96672, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/96672.pdf", "status_text": "Referred to", "journal_page": 346, "committee_id_action": 774, "committee_id_assigned": 797, "result": "P", "vote": {"vote_id": 56142, "president_vote": null, "Yea": [2851, 2852, 2868, 2908], "Nay": [2886, 2916, 2928]}}, {"bill_id": 18070, "action_date": "2003-02-06T07:45:00-06:00", "document_id": 96672, "document_url": 